subSections.title: Usage notes
subSections.text: This character is considered the {{w|traditional Chinese characters|traditional form}} of {{zh-l|产}} in mainland China based on the {{w|zh:新字形|standardized form}} of characters ''({{w|Xin Zixing}})'' in use since 1965.

# (ubu) Birth; infant.
# (umu) Give birth/rise to.
